{% block body %}
    <div class="card-body">
        <section>
            <h2>Overview</h2>
            <p>
                The Car Marketplace Qatar web application is a platform for car auctions, maintenance services, and a
                marketplace. It features maintenance requests, a marketplace for selling cars, live bidding for car
                auctions,
                provision of car parts, car rentals, and registration for car showrooms. The application supports
                multilingual
                interfaces, seamless integration with mobile applications, and multiple payment methods. Standard web
                application features include user authentication, search functionality, notification system, user
                profiles,
                security measures, and customer support.
            </p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Technology Stack</h2>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Framework:</strong> Symfony</li>
                <li><strong>Database:</strong> MySQL</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Targeted Audience</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>Qatar</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Features</h2>

            <ol>
                <li>
                    <strong>Maintenance:</strong>
                    It will provide maintenance services requests, scheduling, a location to meet and type of service
                    required and license plate number
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Marketplace:</strong>
                    The application will offer a platform for selling cars by the users and approved by the admins for
                    publication
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Auction: </strong>
                    The application will facilitate live bidding for car auctions.
                    <ol>
                        <li>Auctions are managed by the admins</li>
                        <li>Bidders need to pay an insurance deposit, designated by the admins before bidding</li>
                        <li>Admins designate the starting bid the targeted price and the budding step value</li>
                        <li>Each car will have an inspection report pdf before the auction</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Provision car parts:</strong> members can request car parts based on their car license
                    number.
                    <ol>
                        <li> User will add his car license number and select from generic parts</li>
                        <li> Admins will search vendors and provide different prices based on car part and it's origin
                        </li>
                        <li> User will select the car parts he desires and where to deliver them</li>
                    </ol>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Car rentals:</strong> just like selling cars but rentals
                </li>
                <li>
                    <strong>Car showrooms:</strong> car showrooms can also register and provide cars for sale or rental
                </li>
            </ol>
        </section>
        <section>

            <h2>Language Support</h2>

            <p>The application will support multilingual interfaces, initially available in two languages.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
